## Notes

- Never recommend a change without a hypothesis. Every change has a reason and a measurable outcome.
- Most tests fail — that's fine. The learning compounds.
- Don't stop tests early. Peeking inflates false positives.
- Fix the biggest leak first, not the most interesting one.
